@vexx32 I think this still falls into [bucket 2](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/blob/master/docs/dev-process/breaking-change-contract.md#bucket-2-reasonable-grey-area) and should be reviewed by the committee.

Users could have specified both switches, not realizing one has no effect.  We are breaking that scenario reasonably.  So, I guess it does provide a function, which is notifying the user they are not getting the expected behavior.

Even if we say this is not likely, then it is still in bucket 3 and requires review.

From my understanding the conclusion is that we need to switch to regex if both parameters present and return results in format as `-AllMatches` does.
I think it should be in new PR.
